  "prompt": "How do I concentrate more on studies?",
  "response": "Here are some tips to improve concentration while studying:\n\n1. Create a study schedule\n- Set specific study times\n- Break study sessions into manageable chunks\n- Use techniques like Pomodoro (25 min study, 5 min break)\n\n2. Optimize your study environment\n- Find a quiet, well-lit space\n- Minimize distractions\n- Keep your study area clean and organized\n\n3. Improve study techniques\n- Use active learning methods\n- Take notes\n- Summarize key points\n- Use mind maps and visual aids\n\n4. Minimize digital distractions\n- Turn off phone notifications\n- Use website blockers\n- Use apps that limit social media time\n\n5. Practice self-care\n- Get enough sleep\n- Exercise regularly\n- Eat a balanced diet\n- Stay hydrated\n\n6. Mental preparation\n- Set clear goals\n- Practice meditation\n- Use positive affirmations\n- Manage stress through relaxation techniques\n\n7. Additional strategies\n- Study in groups\n- Reward yourself after completing tasks\n- Use motivational techniques\n- Identify and address your learning style\n\n8. Consider professional help\n- Seek guidance from counselors\n- Discuss potential attention issues with professionals\n\nRemember, finding what works best for you might take time and experimentation.",
